#TSLDialogues: For the third episode of TSL Dialogues we spoke to Vivek Ramabhadran, Founder of Aulerth to know all about his newest collection launch with ace designer Suneet Varma. Titled Mehr the collection takesinspiration from the Taj Mahal and Mughal artistry, while echoing the philosophy that the duo believes in – beauty starts from within. Here’s what Vivek told The Style List.
.
.
.
#Aulerth #mehrbysuneetverma #Jewellery #TheStyleList #Sustainablejewellery #Newcollection

This Valentine’s Day, we explore the deep connections people share with craft—beyond beauty, beyond trends, into a space where passion meets purpose.

In conversation with Vivek Ramabhadran, Founder & CEO of Aulerth, we dive into his love for sustainable craftsmanship and his mission to reimagine jewelry with a minimal mining footprint. From transforming recycled metals into exquisite pieces to building a future-forward approach to luxury, his journey is a testament to the idea that craft, when done responsibly, can preserve, empower, and endure.

Because true love—for craft, for heritage, for the planet—is always conscious.

latestPosts.caption:
Our founder and CEO, Vivek Ramabhadran, extends his heartfelt New Year greetings to all.

“In 2025, we look forward to being -
in several thousand moments - of sparkle, in your most cherished occasions
in several thousand gifting moments, reflective of your intent to give, love, share
in several thousand moments, where we continue to delve deeper together to stretching the boundaries between conscious consumption and conscious living.

Hand in hand, along with our passionate and growing community, we have embarked on a journey for positive societal impact...and all of this enabled by the power and force of fine design and finesse in craftsmanship, which we bring forth together along with our wonderful creative partners — @jjv.kapurthala, @suneetvarmaofficial, @ekayabanaras, @shivanandnarresh, and @tribebyamrapali, and there’s more to come this year.”

Here’s a sincere wish from all of us,
towards a future that is more conscious,
and a 𝗖𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲, 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗶𝘀 𝗶𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗲𝗱, 𝗣𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗶𝗼𝘂𝘀!

𝗪𝗶𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗹𝗹 𝗮 𝗛𝗮𝗽𝗽𝘆 𝗡𝗲𝘄 𝗬𝗲𝗮𝗿!

Otherwise - the door shutter, the late night Hocco eater, the avocado lover, the perennial salt and lemon adder, popular movie boycotter, Apple Music shuffler, and more … :). I Love you :) ❤️😘😘

𝗔𝘂𝗹𝗲𝗿𝘁𝗵 𝗠𝘂𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀

𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗿 𝗲𝘃𝗶𝗹: 𝗮 𝗹𝘂𝘅𝘂𝗿𝘆 𝗴𝗼𝗼𝗱 𝗼𝗿 𝗮 𝗳𝗮𝘀𝘁-𝗳𝗮𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁?

Vivek Ramabhadran (@vivek.ramabhadran), Founder and CEO of Aulerth, shares his thoughts on whether fast fashion is truly the real environmental villain, or if we’re overlooking the deeper causes behind the industry’s massive environmental impact.

“A fast fashion purchase, costing just a few dollars, might be a one-time wear for some, but for others, it could be something they wear often and consider a more significant purchase. But what about a luxury leather bag that’s only used once? Then how do we define what’s actually fast fashion?”

Watch the full reel and share your thoughts with us in the comment section below.

latestPosts.caption:
We constantly chase our happiness, our dreams. We have our high moments – when we receive something we desire, special moments with those we love, moments of validation and achievement and more. But, we also often fall into the turbulent seas of pain, fear, and doubt. A relentless echo persists: “Why me?” “Why do I have to endure all the pain and suffering?” “Why can’t we just have only the happy or the “high”moments?

In our resistance to the pain, sadness, we chase pleasure and happiness even more, which leads to further pain, sadness and that leads to further turbulence. And we see that we are trapped!!

It is in these depths, we realise a profound truth - the duality of existence - pleasure and pain, happiness and sadness, excitement and disappointment, ecstasy and depression, and more. Both states are 2 sides of the same coin. One can’t be without the other. 

We need answers - we get them not by thinking, but in between our thoughts. 
 
Coming soon at @aulerthofficial

In the past, jewelry was a personal statement, a way to express individuality and creativity. Over time, societal and cultural meanings began to overshadow this joy. Aulerth is on a mission to bring back the personal touch to jewelry, empowering individuals to adorn themselves with pieces that truly reflect their unique spirit.
 
Watch Vivek Ramabhadran (@vivek.ramabhadran), Founder and CEO of Aulerth talk about how Aulerth is redefining the way we experience and perceive jewelry.
